<br>
This topic is the bane of Druids and Wizards always.  And it gets run into the ground every time.  People wonder why Wizards either don't TL or they charge for their TLs, but those same people seem to have no problem charging huge prices for the very same spell.  Then they have the gall to wonder why wizards are so "greedy".  ONE SINGLE WIZARD asks for the going rate, and you assume the the ENTIRE COMMUNITY OF WIZARDS are greedy.  And this comment from someone who owns a wizard is fairly surprising.  Some gaters, like me, don't charge, but ask that a donation be given if they feel like it.  Others don't do it at all.  Gaters are no where required that have to gate people for what ever reason.  And just because you have a wizard doesn't mean that you have an "insider" track into what is being thought of, and the reasons behind what happened.  I know quite a few posters who supposedly "know" how things should be because they have high level wizards as well (I know of one in particular), only to find out that when I reach that point, that their "understanding" was just a load of crap.  <br>
<br>
All in all, he just wanted the going rate, and you didn't like it cuz you didn't get your way.  Hey, happens to me as well.  Sometimes I can't get a rez when I need one.. even when I volunteer to gate them to the location, gate them back, and pay them in the currency of their choice (be it peridots or PP).  But I ain't going to come here and complain how all clerics are losers because one didn't rez me. <p><b>Orakkus Mu'hadeeb</b><br>
<i>Evoker of the 56th Circle of Burning Hellice</i><br>Adventuring for the Triad of Honor.<br><br>

Wizards may not be welcomed in groups.. but we are always welcomed at parties.  Why?  Because we do them all.. and we do them good.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#527129><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/uthecobalwizard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TheCobalWizard</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Squire</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/14/02 10:49:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=498.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: People who rip you off with TLs/Gates</span><hr size=1> I don't go /anon, or /role, but I do not advertise gates, either.  If someone sends me a /tell for a gate or rez, I ignore them.  I always leave /ooc and /shout on, and if someone is offering enough to entice me, or they seem really desperate, I will respond.  It just aggravates me to have people contact me directly.  Most of the time it is because they think that if they ask you directly, you will have a harder time saying no.<br>
<br>
I used to say &quot;sorry, no, I can't,&quot; followed by an explanation of why I couldn't.  Now I just say no, because I realized I am not sorry.  I play 7 characters, 6 of which cannot gate, and that is my choice.  I don't care if a cleric or wizard is sitting right next to me, apparently doing nothing.  I am not going to harangue them for gate/rez, and likewise, I don't feel it is my responsibility to gate/rez/clarity/sow anyone just because I can.<br>
<br>
As for &quot;fees&quot;, I don't initiate them, so I have no fee.  I will not offer if the person isn't offering enough for my time, so that isn't a problem I have had.  I have had people offer to pay, then stand there thinking I would forget.  It is amusing geting a tell when they are left standing there when I gate off.  One SURE way to never get a gate/rez from me is to not offer to compensate me.  I may not take it, but at least you offered, showing that you realize that what I am doing for you is a service. <p>---------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
